  m_text: "The morning sun begins to sixt,\r\nThrough shadows where the ivy grew.\r\nA
    lonely bird begins to fourth,\r\nAbove the grass all wet with dew.\r\n\r\nThe
    garden path is lined with eight,\r\nTall lilies bowing to the breeze.\r\nI\u2019ll
    wait until the hour is three,\r\nTo rest beneath the willow trees."
